Sentence: Do sit down!
Do : auxiliary verb, used for emphasis in imperative mood
sit : main verb, base form, imperative mood
down : adverb, indicates direction
! : punctuation, exclamation mark
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (emphatic)

Sentence: Don't touch the wet paint.
Don't : contraction of "do not", auxiliary verb for negative imperative
touch : main verb, base form, imperative mood
the : definite article, specifies the noun
wet : adjective, describes the noun "paint"
paint : noun, singular, direct object of "touch"
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (negative)

Sentence: Let's go to the park.
Let's : contraction of "let us", first person plural imperative marker
go : main verb, base form, imperative mood
to : preposition, indicates direction
the : definite article, specifies the noun
park : noun, singular, object of the preposition "to"
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: we (included in "Let's")
Mood: imperative (hortatory)

Sentence: Please close the door behind you.
Please : adverb, polite marker for imperative
close : main verb, base form, imperative mood
the : definite article, specifies the noun
door : noun, singular, direct object of "close"
behind : preposition, indicates location
you : pronoun, object of the preposition "behind"
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (polite)

Sentence: Do be careful with that glass!
Do : auxiliary verb, used for emphasis in imperative mood
be : main verb (copula), base form, imperative mood
careful : adjective, subject complement describing the implicit subject
with : preposition, indicates association
that : demonstrative adjective, specifies the noun
glass : noun, singular, object of the preposition "with"
! : punctuation, exclamation mark
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (emphatic)

Sentence: Let him finish his homework first.
Let : main verb, base form, imperative mood
him : pronoun, object of "let"
finish : main verb, base form, bare infinitive complement
his : possessive adjective, modifies "homework"
homework : noun, uncountable, direct object of "finish"
first : adverb, indicates time sequence
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood, commanding regarding "him")
Mood: imperative (permissive)

Sentence: Don't ever speak to me like that again.
Don't : contraction of "do not", auxiliary verb for negative imperative
ever : adverb, emphasizes the negative frequency
speak : main verb, base form, imperative mood
to : preposition, indicates recipient
me : pronoun, object of the preposition "to"
like : preposition, indicates manner
that : demonstrative pronoun, object of the preposition "like"
again : adverb, indicates repetition
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (negative, emphatic)

Sentence: Let's not argue about trivial matters.
Let's : contraction of "let us", first person plural imperative marker
not : adverb, negates the following verb
argue : main verb, base form, imperative mood
about : preposition, indicates topic
trivial : adjective, describes the noun "matters"
matters : noun, plural, object of the preposition "about"
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: we (included in "Let's")
Mood: imperative (negative hortatory)

Sentence: Do try the chocolate cake; it's delicious.
Do : auxiliary verb, used for emphasis in imperative mood
try : main verb, base form, imperative mood
the : definite article, specifies the noun
chocolate : noun acting as adjective, describes "cake"
cake : noun, singular, direct object of "try"
; : punctuation, semicolon
it's : contraction of "it is", pronoun and copula
delicious : adjective, subject complement
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (emphatic suggestion)

Sentence: Never forget where you came from.
Never : adverb, negates the verb absolutely
forget : main verb, base form, imperative mood
where : subordinating conjunction, introduces the clause
you : pronoun, subject of the subordinate clause
came : verb, past tense, predicate of the subordinate clause
from : preposition, part of the phrasal verb "came from"
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (negative absolute)

Sentence: Let the dog out immediately.
Let : main verb, base form, imperative mood
the : definite article, specifies the noun
dog : noun, singular, object of "let"
out : adverb, indicates direction/result
immediately : adverb, indicates time urgency
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (directive)

Sentence: Do not hesitate to call if you need help.
Do : auxiliary verb, part of negative construction
not : adverb, negates the verb
hesitate : main verb, base form, imperative mood
to : particle, marks the infinitive
call : verb, base form, infinitive complement
if : subordinating conjunction, introduces condition
you : pronoun, subject of the subordinate clause
need : verb, present tense, predicate of the subordinate clause
help : noun, uncountable, direct object of "need"
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (negative advice)

Sentence: Let's celebrate our success tonight!
Let's : contraction of "let us", first person plural imperative marker
celebrate : main verb, base form, imperative mood
our : possessive adjective, modifies "success"
success : noun, uncountable, direct object of "celebrate"
tonight : adverb, indicates time
! : punctuation, exclamation mark
Implicit subject: we (included in "Let's")
Mood: imperative (hortatory)

Sentence: Just ignore the noise and keep working.
Just : adverb, softens the command or implies simplicity
ignore : main verb, base form, imperative mood
the : definite article, specifies the noun
noise : noun, uncountable, direct object of "ignore"
and : coordinating conjunction, links two verbs
keep : main verb, base form, imperative mood
working : gerund/participle, complement of "keep"
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (advisory)

Sentence: Don't let the opportunity slip away.
Don't : contraction of "do not", auxiliary verb for negative imperative
let : main verb, base form, imperative mood
the : definite article, specifies the noun
opportunity : noun, singular, object of "let"
slip : verb, base form, bare infinitive complement
away : adverb, indicates direction/result
. : punctuation, period
Implicit subject: you (understood)
Mood: imperative (negative warning)
